      "name": "FDA pump hemolysis benchmark comparison — 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 flow-speed combinations. Mean absolute error 38% at MRL 5 operating envelope; prediction intervals from Monte Carlo propagation of viscosity and shear-stress model uncertainty span the experimental range but do not achieve required agreement tolerance."
